aes::semantic(userset_ref_to_permission)

  × userset references a computed permission, not a relation
   ╭─[test.aes:7:22]
 6 │ type user {
 7 │   let owner = group::read;
   ·                      ──┬─
   ·                        ╰── this is a `def` on `group`, but only `let` relations can be used in userset references
 8 │ }
   ╰────
  help: userset syntax `type::member` requires `member` to be a `let` relation, not a `def` permission
